<li><a href="http://www.cbi.umn.edu/oh/display.phtml?id=100" class="external text" title="http://www.cbi.umn.edu/oh/display.phtml?id=100" rel="nofollow">Oral history interview with Ivan Sutherland</a>, <a href="/wiki/Charles_Babbage_Institute" title="Charles Babbage Institute">Charles Babbage Institute</a>, University of Minnesota. Sutherland describes his tenure as head of ARPA's Information Processing Techniques Office (IPTO) from 1963 to 1965, including new projects in graphics and networking.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cbi.umn.edu/oh/display.phtml?id=108" class="external text" title="http://www.cbi.umn.edu/oh/display.phtml?id=108" rel="nofollow">Oral history interview with Charles A. Csuri</a>, <a href="/wiki/Charles_Babbage_Institute" title="Charles Babbage Institute">Charles Babbage Institute</a>, University of Minnesota. Csuri recounts his art education and explains his transition to computer graphics in the mid 1960s, after receiving a National Science Foundation grant for research in graphics.</li>
